Miniemoney, a fintech-edtech hybrid company, has launched a family finance mobile application that allows parents and guardians to save for their kids, According to the firm, the app will provide financial services such as access to debit cards, savings accounts, in-app cash transfers, and financial learning to kids and teenagers. In a statement, the firm said, “Miniemoney’s MVP launches with features such as EarnIT, which allows kids and teens to earn money from completing chores and tasks assigned to them by a parent or guardian. “EarnIT can also be used to reward youngsters for academic or related successes. Other features include Minie Wallet, Minie Transfers, Kids’ Savings Account, and in-app quizzes and puzzles. The app is divided into two journeys: the parent journey and the youngster journey. “Youngster accounts must be verified by a parent or legal guardian before accessing certain features, however, in-app learning is available to every youngster with or without parental verification.” The Chief Executive Officer and founder of the firm, Gbolahan Faniran, added, “This is more than just a passion project for me; it’s a vision that will take the average Nigerian family into the future. Progress, like charity, begins at home.”